This paper proposes a new family of invertible transformations for flow-based generative models, which are commonly used in machine learning for modeling complex distributions. The paper specifically focuses on image datasets such as ImageNet, indicating a strong connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the limitations of autoregressive models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and time series analysis (cs.IT). The proposed method combines the strengths of flow-based and autoregressive models, making it relevant to a broad range of machine learning applications, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, which covers machine learning and statistical learning theory.
